 page the assets are used on\r\n\r\n### Expected result\r\n\r\nasset will be delivered with no query string like or use the json manifest like so:  \r\n\r\n``<script src=\"/theme/myTheme/dist/app.js\"></script>`` \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Actual result\r\n\r\nthe assets are still served with bolt's version strategy or ignores the json manifest option.  \r\n\r\n------\r\n\r\n\r\nThe reason this happens is bolt uses a different way to get the configs for the asset fuction.  \r\n  \r\nSymfony uses the above examples and bolt uses   \r\n\r\n```yaml  \r\nassets:\r\n   theme:\r\n        json_manifest_path: \"/dist/manifest.json\"\r\n``` \r\n\r\nThe ``framework``,  and ``packages`` config options are not present in the way bolt applies the versioning strategy, and is not mentioned in the docs that they differ and since the symfony docs are linked too one would assume that bolt follows the same conventions.  \r\n\r\nI noticed this after I was linked to the asset provider https://github.com/bolt/bolt/blob/master/src/Provider/AssetServiceProvider.php#L60 on slack \r\n\r\n\r\n","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7482","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7482/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7482/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7482/events","html_url":"https://github.com/bolt/bolt/issues/7482","id":322766824,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzMjI3NjY4MjQ=","number":7482,"title":"Missing quotes in MySQL queries","user":{"login":"otrelin","id":15085327,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MDg1MzI3","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/15085327?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/otrelin","html_url":"https://github.com/otrelin","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/otrelin/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/otrelin/following{/other_user}","gists_url":