mary\r\n\r\nPreview button doesn't work on Chrome if you have an field with HTML in the content type editor. It can be a field for embeding an iframe or just a Tweet added with the build-in embeding tool.\r\n\r\n### Specifics\r\n\r\nThe [`DisableXssProtectionListener`](https://github.com/bolt/bolt/blob/14b3ec1019fd3a6af91ff92e246ec9081e50e49f/src/EventListener/DisableXssProtectionListener.php) which adds that header is runed when the current route name is in the array defined in the [`disable_xss_protection_routes`](https://github.com/bolt/bolt/blob/180a3a4c21e37fe55a7c681657f53e1ada682c81/src/Provider/EventListenerServiceProvider.php#L30). The problem is when you click the Preview button Bolt is using `contentlink` route, not the `preview` one. I checked it by inserting `dump($route)` in the mentioned listener below 44 line.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n* Add to any content type a text field\r\n* Go to record editor\r\n* Put in that field `<iframe src=\"http://google.com\"></iframe>`\r\n* Click the preview button\r\n\r\n### Expected result\r\n\r\nPreview of that record should be displayed\r\n\r\n### Actual result\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6128754/38773669-cbf18c98-4052-11e8-900e-45cda3b65b5d.png)\r\n\r\nHow to fix it (temporarly)?\r\n-------------\r\n\r\nIf you have a bundled extension you can overwrite there the list of not protected routes\r\n```\r\n$app['disable_xss_protection_routes'] = [\r\n    'preview',\r\n    'fileedit',\r\n    'contentlink' // <= that helps\r\n];\r\n```\r\nHowever this is probably a workaround and just the route used for previews is wrong. That is also why I didn't create a PR.","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7437","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7437/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7437/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/re