rs/Boorj/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Boorj/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Boorj/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Boorj/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Boorj/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Boorj/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Boorj/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Boorj/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Boorj/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2018-03-30T14:00:10Z","updated_at":"2018-05-31T07:15:18Z","closed_at":"2018-05-30T12:54:42Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Idea: make some image processing available for thumbnails.\r\n---\r\nSometimes you need to watermark an image. Often it's necessary not for small thumbs, but for big images (`thumbnail(image, 1200, 600, resize)`).  \r\n\r\nSo i found the way to do it in bundle/extension.\r\n\r\nIt's initialized this way\r\n<details><summary>MyThumbsExtension.php</summary>\r\n\r\n```php\r\n// Somewhere deep in extension\r\n\r\n    public function getServiceProviders()\r\n    {\r\n        $app = $this->getContainer();\r\n\r\n        $app['thumbnails.creator'] = $app->share($app->extend('thumbnails.creator', function ($creator, $app) {\r\n            $webPath = $app['resources']->getPath('web');\r\n             // my way for current project. It watermarks file it has img_ inside. \r\n            $options = [\r\n                \"watermark\" => [\r\n                    \"filePath\" =>  $webPath . '/i/watermark1.png',\r\n                    \"conditions\" => [\r\n                        \"pattern\" => '/img_/i',\r\n                        \"parameters\" => [\r\n                            \"filePath\" => $webPath . '/i/watermark1.png',\r\n                        ],\r\n                    ],\r\n                ],\r\n            ];\r\n            return new Creator2($app['thumbnails.limit_upscaling'], $app['imagine.svg'], null, $options);\r\n        }));\r\n\r\n```\r\n</details>\r\n\r\nAnd here's the code itself\r\n<details><summary>Creator2.php</summary>\r\n\r\n```php\r\n<?php\r\n\r\nnamespace Mapple\\Boltstrap;\r\n\r\nuse Bolt\\Thumbs\\Color;\r\nuse Bolt\\Thumbs\\Creator;\r\nuse Bolt\\Thumbs\\ImageResource;\r\nuse Bolt\\Thumbs\\Transaction;\r\nuse Contao\\ImagineSvg\\Imagine as SvgImagine;\r\n\r\nclass Creator2 extends Creator\r\n{\r\n    /** @var  $options */\r\n    protected $options;\r\n\r\n    public function __construct($limitUpscaling = true, SvgImagine $svgImagine = null, Color $background = null, $options) {\r\n        parent::__construct($limitUpscaling, $svgImagine, $background);\r\n        $this->options = $options;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * {@inheritdoc}\r\n     */\r\n    public function create(Transaction $transaction) {\r\n        $imageData = parent::create($transaction);\r\n\r\n        $im = ImageResource::createFromString($imageData);\r\n\r\n        try {\r\n            $stamp = ImageResource::createFromFile( $this->options['watermark']['filePath'] );\r\n        }\r\n        catch (Exception $e) {\r\n            return $imageData;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        $this->watermark($im, $stamp);\r\n\r\n        return $im->toString();\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    /**\r\n     * watermark - mutates first resource (!)\r\n     *\r\n     * @param ImageResource $destImg    -\r\n     * @param ImageResource $stampImg   -\r\n     * @param int           $margeX     - horizontal margin (inactive for position === 'center')\r\n     * @param int           $margeY     - vertical margin (inactive for position === 'center')\r\n     * @param string        $position   -\r\n     * @return ImageResource\r\n     */\r\n    public function watermark(ImageResource $destImg, ImageResource $stampImg, $margeX = 10, $margeY = 10, $position = 'right bottom'){\r\n        /* @see http://php.net/manual/en/image.examples-watermark.php */\r\n\r\n        $stampW = $stampImg->getDimensions()->getWidth();\r\n        $stampH = $stampImg->getDimensions()->getHeight();\r\n\r\n        $imageW = $destImg->getDimensions()->getWidth();\r\n        $imageH = $destImg->getDimensions()->getHeight();\r\n\r\n        switch ($position){\r\n            case \"bottom right\" :\r\n            case \"right bottom\" :\r\n                $watermarkX = $imageW - $stampW - $margeX;\r\n                $watermarkY = $imageH - $stampH - $margeY;\r\n                break;\r\n\r\n            case \"top right\" :\r\n            case \"right top\" :\r\n                $watermarkX = $imageW - $stampW - $margeX;\r\n                $watermarkY = $margeY;\r\n                break;\r\n\r\n            case \"bottom left\" :\r\n            case \"left bottom\" :\r\n                $watermarkX = $margeX;\r\n                $watermarkY = $imageH - $stampH - $margeY;\r\n                break;\r\n\r\n            case \"top left\" :\r\n            case \"left top\" :\r\n                $watermarkX = $margeX;\r\n                $watermarkY = $margeY;\r\n                break;\r\n\r\n            default:\r\n                $watermarkX = 0;\r\n                $watermarkY = 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        imagecopy(\r\n            $destImg->getResource(),\r\n            $stampImg->getResource(),\r\n            $watermarkX, $watermarkY,\r\n            0, 0, $stampW, $stampH\r\n        );\r\n        return $destImg;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n</details>\r\n\r\nThis code changes `Bolt\\Thumbs\\Creator.php`, but there's a better idea. Let people use additional plugins for that.\r\n\r\n\r\nFor example, we modify original `Creator::create`\r\n```php\r\n   public function create(Transaction $transaction)\r\n    {\r\n        $this->verifyInfo($transaction);\r\n        $this->autoscale($transaction);\r\n        $this->checkForUpscale($transaction);\r\n        $data = $this->resize($transaction);\r\n        return $data;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nto this\r\n```php\r\n   // adding $this->preprocessor and $this->postprocessor in __construct, and then:\r\n   public function create(Transaction $transaction)\r\n    {\r\n        $this->verifyInfo($transaction);\r\n        $this->autoscale($transaction);\r\n        $this->checkForUpscale($transaction);\r\n\r\n        if ($this->preprocessor) {\r\n            $data = $this->preprocessor($transaction);\r\n            $data = $this->resize( $data ) ;\r\n            // resize is polymorphic and accepts $data and $transaction, or \r\n            // we can split it\r\n        }\r\n        else {\r\n            $data = $this->resize($transaction);\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        if ($this->postprocessor) {\r\n            // if we have postprocessor - apply to resized image\r\n            $data = $this->postprocessor($data); \r\n        }\r\n\r\n        return $data;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n```\r\n(read comments in code).\r\n\r\nIf we will have processor options and we can $app->share($app['thumbnails.creator'],...) by adding pre/post processing options - it will allow us to extend Thumbnails.\r\n\r\n### Case\r\nLet's assume we want to add watermarks.\r\nPreprocessors is useful if you know the _original size_ and you have one size watermark. You add watermark to original, then resize, then return resized image in `Bolt\\Thumb\\Controller` response.\r\nPostprocessors if you know the _final size_ of image and you don't want to resize the watermark stamp. So you know final resolution (1200×800px) and just stamp your image on photo and return.\r\n\r\n#### problem\r\nAccess to original files is not restricted in current setup.\r\nSo you can\r\n1. **restrict it in server setup (apache http.conf, apache htaccess, nginf config)**\r\n2. **upload outside web root (`/public/`)**\r\n  this needs a special controller to upload, set permissions for editors, add backend pages. \r\n3. **make secret path**\r\n  like `/public/very_secret_path12378923/secret_folder` and then provide all processed thumbnails from that path. This is not bullitproof option, for an example: if you send a link to one of those files via skype or other messagers, bingbot will parse that image and put to index. Anyway, access will not be 100% secure. \r\n\r\nFeel free to suggest something else.\r\n\r\n#### problem solution\r\nOption 2 Looks good to me. Any way we'll need a distinct controller, which allows us to upload to secret folder. And then, we can safely upload anything we want. Here's the [example in Boltforms](https://github.com/bolt/boltforms/blob/4.2/src/Controller/UploadManagement.php) (thanks to @rossriley for referencing it).\r\n\r\nSo .. the easiest way to me is:\r\n\r\nSuggestion\r\n---\r\n#### provide a runway for processors:\r\n- create `$app['thumbnails.preprocessors']` and $app['thumbnails.postprocessors']. Too queues for processing. Probably with priority. Or we can join that to one queue and have positive and negative priorities (10, -10). Thumb resize will have 0 priority\r\n- initialize `Bolt\\Thumbs\\Response` inside `ThumbnailsServiceProvider` with those pre/postprocessor queues. `[ { priority : -10 /*default, optional*/ ,   function processor1  } ]\r\n- Here's an idea for processor interface:\r\n    ```php\r\n    function processor1(ImageResource $im, Transaction $transaction) {\r\n        if (preg_match(..., $transaction->requestPath, ...)) {\r\n          // watermark here, change colors.\r\n        }\r\n       return $im;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    ```\r\n    It gets original file data (in transaction), and it gets an image resource in bolt's `ImageResource` format. \r\n    Notice, that it gets file data from original `Creator`, it doesn't read file from disk.\r\n\r\nThis explains how it could work _without_ security restrictions.\r\n\r\n#### security\r\nIf user did set up an option for _secure storage_ in `config.yml`, for example `config.thumbnails.secure_storage: 'root/secure_files'` we can add SecureStorageProvider, which\r\n- creates backend route+page with filemanager (or adds folder to current filemanager)\r\n- In `ThumbnailsProvider` we tell `Bolt\\Thumb\\Response`, that \"if we have request for this pattern (like `/thumbs\\/.*\\/secure_file/` \" - take data from secured folder.\r\n\r\n\r\nBonus\r\n---\r\n- We can make watermarking as default function in `Bolt\\Thumbs` . And turn it to queue by string options (not passing a function parameter). For example in `config.yml`\r\n```yml\r\nthumbnails:\r\n    alias:\r\n        wtrmrk: {resize: '800x600', stamp_image: 'files/123.png' }\r\n# OR \r\n    # first we add watermark to original (priority 100 goes BEFORE resizing)\r\n   processors: \r\n    - builtin_processor_name: 'watermark'\r\n      prority: 100\r\n      options:\r\n          stamp_image: 'files/123.png'\r\n          margin: [10, 10]\r\n          position: 'bottom left'\r\n\r\n    # then we desaturate resized image (prority -100 goes AFTER resizing)\r\n    - builtin_processor_name: 'blackandwhite'\r\n      prority: 100\r\n      options: ~\r\n# or \r\n    # syntactic sugar with string parameters\r\n    processors: ['blackandwhite', {name: watermark, file: 'files/123.png'}] \r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Also, we can make aliases for special secured folders. Like `/thumbs/photos/image123.jpg` will give you watermarked *resized* to 1000×800 image from `/web/files/special_folder/image123.jpg` or `/secure_files_not_inside_web/image123.jpg/`\r\n    \r\nBonus 2\r\n---\r\nSecure storage in core could be a big bonus for Bolt (if server allows). If `/thumbs` are not 1-to-1 connected to `/files` - It allows later \r\n- to create unique filenames, for example `/thumbs/secure/1000x800r/image-fd1c2a4b6e.jpg` - if you have a controller, of course\r\n\r\n","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7419","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bolt/bolt/issues/7419/lab